Name: HPE BIOS Message Registry
Description: This registry defines the messages for HPE BIOS.

MessagesMaxSizeExceeded.Description: Indicates that the last configuration change attempted by the user resulted in a number of error messages that exceeded the maximum storage capacity alloted for messages corresponding to this resource.
MessagesMaxSizeExceeded.Message: The messages array has been truncated because the last configuration change resulted in too many error messages.
MessagesMaxSizeExceeded.Resolution: Inspect the last configuration change request for issues that may be generating errors, compare the request against the resource's schema, then retry the configuration change.

UnsupportedAMPConfiguration.Description: Indicates that the user provided Advanced Memory Protection (AMP) option is not appropriate for this memory configuration, as the underlying hardware does not support it.
UnsupportedAMPConfiguration.Message: Underlying hardware does not support the requested AMP configuration, the settings are invalid.
UnsupportedAMPConfiguration.Resolution: Ensure that the current memory configuration meets the requirements of the requested value before applying the settings.

UnsupportedProcessorRaplValue.Description: Indicates that the user provided Running Average Power Limit (RAPL) value could not be applied due to inherent processor power limitation. The value may be out of bounds or invalid.
UnsupportedProcessorRaplValue.Message: Underlying processor does not support the requested value.
UnsupportedProcessorRaplValue.Resolution: Ensure that the processor supports the requested value and that it is within the supported bounds before applying the settings.

UnsupportedDramRaplValue.Description: Indicates that the user provided Running Average Power Limit (RAPL) value could not be applied due to inherent DRAM power limitation. The value may be out of bounds or invalid.
UnsupportedDramRaplValue.Message: Underlying DRAM does not support the requested value.
UnsupportedDramRaplValue.Resolution: Ensure that the requested value is within the supported bounds before applying the settings.

LicenseFailure.Description: Indicates that the setting could not be changed due to a licensing requirement that was not met.
LicenseFailure.Message: Cannot update setting due to a licensing failure.
LicenseFailure.Resolution: Ensure that proper license is installed.
